From: acb@zikzak.apana.org.au (Andrew Bulhak)
Crossposted-To: apana.linux,aus.computers.linux
Subject: Re: pl14 and virtual consoles
Date: 4 Dec 1993 12:50:11 GMT

Matthew Jackson (mjj@emjay.apana.org.au) wrote:

: I have an interesting problem here. I tend to use lots of virtual
: consoles and need to keep at least one spare for XFree86. So I change
: the number of consoles in include/linux/tty.h to 12

: Now when I run pl14 with 12 consoles I get one of two effects:

: ii) I get login prompts on the specified consoles but when I try to
:     login I don't get a password prompt just ld.so.1.3 (yes it is
:     installed!)

No kidding? I have pl13, and that happens in different circumstances. When I am
compiling something big (i.e., a kernel or Wine), sometimes the compiler 
freezes; I go into another virtual console and login, but the password prompt
does not appear until I press ^C on the compiler. Note that this only happens
on newer kernels; pl7A doesn't do it (and it is smaller); perhaps this is a
side-effect of Linux now being written in C++.....

                                        -- A.


