From: jmorriso@rflab.ee.ubc.ca (John Paul Morrison)
Crossposted-To: comp.os.linux.help
Subject: Re: Sun rup-like program for linux?
Date: 5 Dec 1993 00:07:24 GMT

In article <2dp21i$fc4@geraldo.cc.utexas.edu>,
Daniel M. Coleman <dcoleman@mbs.telesys.utexas.edu> wrote:
:I'm looking for a program for linux similar to rup on Suns, which does this:
:
:sylvester.cc.utexas.edu% rup ccwf
:        ccwf    up          23:53,    load average: 7.32, 6.71, 6.54
:sylvester.cc.utexas.edu%
:
:Has anyone found and successfully compiled such a thing?

I have. I put rup.tar.gz up for anonymous ftp on rflab.ee.ubc.ca:/pub/rup.tar.gz.

It includes a binary and a manual page. I seem to have misplaced the source
code but it wasnt hard to compile; I got the source from the Net/FreeBSD
distribution.

The binary is statically linked due to an annoying RPC bug
(pmap_rmt.c) (well, not really a bug, it was just compiled with the
wrong #defines) in the Linux libc. 

Anyway, try it and hopefully it will work for you. rflab.ee.ubc.ca is a Linux
machine connected to a net with a bunch of Suns on it, and rup works fine for
me. (if it doesnt work, check your routing; try running as root too)

:
